<p><a href="https://github.com/brontosaurusrex/postbang/blob/master/.vimrc">postbang/blob/master/.vimrc</a></p>

<h2 id="copypaste">copy/paste</h2>

<p>Debian/openbox/urxvt/vim8</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>apt install vim-gtk # vim-gtk3
ctrl+alt+v &lt; should now work to paste stuff from other clipboard, or
middle-mouse-button &lt; paste behaves differently
"+p &lt; paste from other clipboard 
"+gp &lt; this horror should paste as well
"+yy &lt; copy current line
"+y20 &lt; copy this and 20 lines below
:help "+ &lt; actually finds clipboard related help
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Possibly worth checking gvim for some ideas and to see what is terminal to blame for and what is vimâ€™s fault. This is a huge showstopper.</p>

<h2 id="spellcheck">spellcheck</h2>

